Sentencas: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-delta (LCN64) was prepared through the polymeric steric entrapment precursor route with Polyvinyl alcohol (PVA) as the entrapment agent and was evaluated as a contact material between the metallic interconnect and the cathode in planar intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell stacks (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ratio of PVA to metal nitrates and the calcination temperature of the precursor were optimized for the process.
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity and thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of the synthesized LCN64 and its chemical compatibility with SUS 430 were also characterized.
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that 1:4 is a proper ratio of PVA to metal nitrates for process control and safety management; and calcination of the precursor at temperatures above 650 degrees C leads to formation of single perovskite phase LCN64.
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of fully sintered LCN64 is above 1150 S cm(-1) in the temperature range between 100 degrees C and 800 degrees C, which is higher than those of conventional contact materials La1-xSrxMnO3 (LSM) and LaNiyFe1-yO3 (LNF).
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC is 17.22 x 10(-6) K-1 at temperatures below 900 degrees C, which is higher than those of the metallic interconnect and cell components.
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Mn and Cr elements contained in SUS 430 migrated into the porous LCN64 layer at 800 degrees C without chemically forming resistive phases.
Titulo: LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
